---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — MakerPortal';
const description =
  'How MakerPortal handles data on the hub and in our apps. On-device first where possible, transparent cloud disclosure for agentic features like AuraLinter. Affiliate disclosure + export soft-gate.';
const updated = 'July 19, 2026';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="reading-paper flex-1 border-b reading-line">
    <header class="border-b reading-line">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
        <p class="section-kicker">Legal · Privacy</p>
        <h1 class="reading-ink mt-5 text-balance text-[clamp(2.4rem,5vw,3.5rem)] font-[700] leading-[0.95] tracking-[-0.05em]">Privacy policy.</h1>
        <p class="mt-5 text-[1.05rem] leading-[1.7]" style="color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--mp-paper-ink) 85%, var(--mp-paper-muted))">
          We design for minimal data. Many apps run fully on-device; AuraLinter and other agentic features use transparent cloud with clear retention. This hub collects only what you deliberately send.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 font-mono text-[0.65rem] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] reading-muted">Updated {updated}</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <div class="prose-paper mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-14 sm:px-8 sm:py-20">
        <h2>Scope</h2>
        <p>This policy covers www.makerportal.ai (the hub) and describes how MakerPortal studio products approach privacy. Individual app subdomains may publish product-specific notices; where they conflict, the product notice controls for that app.</p>

        <h2>Hub website</h2>
        <p>We do not use advertising trackers or analytics SDKs that profile you across the web. Contact form submissions are processed to respond to your message (including spam prevention). Server logs may include standard technical data (IP, user agent) for security and reliability.</p>
        <p>Theme preference is stored in <code>localStorage</code> on your device only — it never leaves your browser.</p>

        <h2>Applications</h2>
        <p>Most MakerPortal apps are built for on-device processing where possible. AuraLinter and future agentic titles use cloud for audio upload, LangGraph orchestration, and clang++ verification — with temporary file retention (30min sync, 4h long jobs) and run records disclosed in each product’s privacy policy. We do not sell personal data and disclose cloud use per-app.</p>

        <h2 id="affiliates">Affiliate disclosure</h2>
        <p>Some resource, playground, or shop links are affiliate links. If you purchase through them, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. We only recommend tools we believe are useful. Affiliate relationships never require us to share your personal browsing data with partners beyond what the merchant’s own checkout requires.</p>
        <p class="mt-3"><strong class="text-primary-text">Approved partners today:</strong></p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
          <li><strong>Amazon Associates</strong> — tag <code>engineersport-20</code>. Commission varies by category (often ~1–4.5% on books/tools/electronics). 24h cookie; Creators API cache is build-time only, no runtime calls (D-015).</li>
          <li><strong>SparkFun Affiliate</strong> — referral code <code>rOtrc44SZw</code> (<code>?ref=</code> on sparkfun.com URLs). <strong>10% on SparkFun Original products</strong>; third-party catalog items (e.g. Raspberry Pi boards, Jetson, Teensy) are tracked but may pay $0 under SparkFun’s program rules.</li>
          <li><strong>PCBWay Referral</strong> — <code>https://pcbway.com/g/VJp6Xm</code> — friend gets $5 new-user credit, you get $10 coupon + 5% of 1st order cash (excludes coupons/shipping/components/fees). Live 2026-07-19, low effort. Shared Projects (10% PCB + 10% SMT) still pending — needs real boards, see roadmap.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-[0.9rem]">Pending / shelved: <strong>PCBWay Shared Projects</strong> (10% + 10% recurring) — needs real KiCad + Gerbers + manual review, roadmap P5 deferred until traffic; <strong>JLCPCB</strong> Brand Advocate / referral — same audience as PCBWay, low ROI until 10k sessions, shelved; <strong>Lemon Squeezy Shop + Buttondown Newsletter</strong> — shelved until Google legitimacy / traffic (forms show "Coming soon", export gates work via localStorage only). Code stub-ready in <code>src/data/affiliate-links.ts</code> + <code>FabOrderPanel.astro</code> + <code>ButtondownSignup.astro</code>. See <code>docs/MONETIZATION.md</code>.</p>
        <p class="mt-2">Links use <code>rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer"</code>. We do not use undisclosed native ads.</p>

        <h3 class="mt-8 text-[1.1rem] font-semibold">Export gate & email (soft list)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">Simulator exports (RTOS FreeRTOSConfig.h, SI stackup CSV, SLAM trajectory CSV, PID gains JSON, antenna array JSON, Verilog RTL) have two paths:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1.5 pl-5">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> watermarked file (small footer <code>makerportal.ai</code> brand line) — always available, no email.</li>
          <li><strong>Clean:</strong> watermark removed after soft email unlock. Email is stored in <code>localStorage</code> key <code>mp_export_email_{"{sim}"}</code> + unlock flag <code>mp_export_unlock_{"{sim}"}</code> per simulator. If Buttondown username is configured, we also POST to Buttondown embed endpoint (<code>privacy-first mode</code>, no tracking pixels per D-014) with tag = sim id.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">No hard paywall, no Clerk. You can re-lock via DevTools → Application → Local Storage. Analytics events <code>export_gate_unlock</code>, <code>export_download</code>, <code>gear_click</code>, <code>kit_cta_click</code>, <code>fab_*_click</code> are first-party <code>CustomEvent('mp:analytics')</code> — privacy-safe, no third-party ad pixels.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Privacy questions: <a href="/contact">Contact the studio</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
